  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> </font><b>Coriolanus</b><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>Coriolanus, who acted out of pride rather than duty,\n        is an obvious example of a man locked in the prison of\n        his own self. He led the enemy against his native city\n        out of injured pride (cf. Shakespeare, <i>Coriolanus</i>).\n        (NA)</p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td> </td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Coriolanus Coriolanus, who acted out of pride rather than duty, is an obvious example of a man locked in the prison of his own self. He led the enemy against his native city out of injured pride (cf. Shakespeare, Coriolanus ). (NA) back to \"The Waste Land\"",
